reviewText: My son is 6 and he loves lbt.  We have every dvd of the movies and tv shows that are out right now.  This dvd has 4 episodes: Search for the Sky Color Stones, The Amazing Threehorn Girl, Days of Rising Waters and Return to Hanging Rock.  These shows are a great continuation for the lbt series.
This is a very good movie for children, I even enjoyed this movie with my daughter.

I bought a lot of these for my children. They love the Land Before time dvds. I would recommend them for anyone whose little ones love dinosaurs. It is a very good dinosaur show for children to watch.
My 3 year old daughter loves this series. She dances along with the songs, and there are DVD extras of pictures you can print out to color--another hit.
I get this for my nephew as a gift since he kept watching the very first one, the ones that came out on vhs..turns out he really loves it.
My kids love this series.  They were 2 and 4 years old when I bought it and thus kept their interest in dinos alive.
Bought this movie for my granddaughter as she wanted all of them.  She just loves them. Would tell other about them and where to find them.
These movies are great. They were very reasonable,a great gift,and a all around fun kids movie. My grand kids can't get enough of them. I'm trying to collect them all.
My 3 year old twins LOVE the land before time cartoons. We have 5 or 6 different DVDS and they will sit and watch them again and again for hours. Really great for kids!

I loved the full length feature as a child and my daughter (4) loves it too.  This DVD includes multiple stories that she doesn't seem to get tired of.  If your kids like dinosaurs, they're sure to like this too.
This has always been a favorite movie theme for me.  With this copy, I now have the entire series, my grandchildren are learning serious life lessons from them.
My kids love this series of shows.  The short episodes are great when we need a change of pace from the longer movies.
This Land before Time series is especially attractive for a young imagination. Our 3 year old grandson enjoys each episode and gains a life lesson from each.
